    <name>
      <text>5.3.15 (Solve to scale trig)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Find the values of \(a,b,c\) such that the function \(f(x) = a + b \cos(cx)\) has range \( {@A@}\leq y \leq{@A + 2*B@}\), and has period \({@C*180@}\) degrees.</p>
<p></p>
\(a = \) [[input:ans1]]; [[validation:ans1]]
<p></p>
\(b = \) [[input:ans2]]; [[validation:ans2]]<br>
<p></p>
\(c= \) [[input:ans3]]. [[validation:ans3]]<br>
<p></p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>A function is \(p\)-periodic if \(f(x+p) = f(x)\) for all \(x\). We want \(c\) so that \(\cos(c(x+ {@C@}\cdot 180^\circ)) = \cos(cx)\) for all \(x\).&nbsp; Since \(\cos\) is \(360^\circ\)-periodic, and \(\cos(c(x + {@C@}\cdot 180^\circ))&nbsp; = \cos(cx+ {@C@}c 180^\circ)\) we see that we need \(c={@ta3@}\). The function \(\cos({@ta3@}x)\) takes values between \(-1\) and \(1\), so the function \({@B@}\cos({@ta3@}x)\) takes values between \({@-B@}\) and \({@B@}\).&nbsp; Therefore the function \(f(x) ={@ (A+B) @}+ {@B@}\cos ({@ta3@}x)\) takes values between \({@A@}\) and \({@A + 2*B@}\).&nbsp; So \(f\) is as required when \(a = {@ta1@}\), \(b = {@ta2@}\), and \(c={@ta3@}\).<br></p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
